reviews.reviewText:
The receptionist was efficient and nice.
Nurse Shirley was so kind and professional. She was also so empathetic with my husband who was very distressed.
The PA was also very professional and to the point, while still showing sincere concern.
We will definitely come back because I know my husband took what they said to heart and took much of their advice. I sincerely hope we will be back soon and you will diligently help my husband back to health.
Thank you,
The Olsons

My experience was great. I had an awesome team of nurses that took great care of me. Dr Hamet you are wonderful. I would recommend people to come here at any given time for your care. Thanks, you all ROCKS!!!
Everyone was professional and kind! Love Dr. Hamat and Rhonda!!!
Everyone was kind, caring, and friendly. I had sn excellent experience.

Personable and efficient staff.
I felt like the staff knew each other well and had worked there for a decent amount of time which allowed them great continuity .
Dr. Hamat spoke with me like a friend, listened to my concerns and offered insight as well as a proactive plan moving forward.
Each person took great care in managing my time there efficiently as well as their own. I felt respected as a patient and client through every step.
It is so rare to find a well run business and the same can be said for medical practices in many cases. It was great to be more than a number. This experience was noteworthy. I will only use their office when possible in the future.
Thank you !
Was very informative about the procedure
Everyone in the office is wonderful and care about their patients! If you need a colon screening or have any GI issues, I would recommend making an appointment now!
I get a good experince they are a good team ando are ready to help You feeling confortable
wow great place for a eye examination  very informative  great personal
I recommend Dr. Mahmoud. He listen, answer all of my questions. Explain my procedure very well.

Very good experience...everyone
Friendly and efficient...Dr Hamat was great, as usual. Looks like my liver problem will be challenging.

These doctors are awesome!! So kind and polite!! They really listen to every word and complaint!! The office personnel are also just wonderful!! It’s a terrible place to have to go to but they sure make it worth the trip!

1st visit to this location. Very nice staff. They were running about 15 minutes late and was kind enough to inform me of that. Infusion nurse explained everything well and answered any questions I had.
Unfortunately this is the second time I waited over an hour in the treatment room and never saw a physician. Twice is sufficient for me. Good luck to the Dr.'s and staff.
Nursing great! Scheduling department a big egg 0. Can’t recommend them to anyone, because scheduling department doesn’t exist!
My visit was great. Personnel were very friendly and courteous facility was spotless waiting time was less than 5 minutes and the doctor made me feel comfortable and was trustworthy.
Good luck having a call back if  you leave a message ,you will not get a call back .
Great, Dr is really helpful and knowledgeable
Wonderful personal. My bist was done timely and informative.
Very good experience.  They are always friendly and the facility is clean and comfortable.  I waited less than 10 minutes in the waiting room but over fifteen in the exam room.  The PA was good.
Kind of confusing. Never had this kind of visit before.

I had a colonoscopy on 7/5/22.
The receptionist was very nice.
The staff was professional and concerned and very warm. Dr Wright and Dr Reddy both introduced themselves before the procedure and Dr. Reddy talked to me after the procedure.
All in all they made the procedure pleasant. I would recommend them.
Both Dr Hamat and his Med Student were very gracious. They actually sat down, listened and talked with me about my gastro problems. I feel confident that, now, I can get some relief.
Very comfortable environment everyone was very nice 😊
As always , excellent care ; compassionate staff . Thankyou !
The Doctor’s assistance was very nice the nurse was very friendly and the lady that took my blood was very polite everyone was very professional.
Check in was easy. Employees friendly and helpful
Everyone treated me with respect as a person and not as if I were a number. I will recommend family and friends to your facility.
Quick easy checkin. Dr. Hamat was attentive and informative. Scheduled test to be done soon.
Dr..Hamat was very inquiry based in regards  to understanding my symptoms.. We wanted make sure he completely  understood  my case..For this reason, I would highly  recommend  him to my friends

reviews.reviewAuthor: The Music Man The Music Man
reviews.reviewText: The tech was a little dry. I guess she see a lot of patients and don't have time to be just a little bit personal
I’m grateful for Dr. Mahmoud! He is an excellent doctor with knowledge, patience and kindness. Thank you for all that you do! Blessings.
Staff is friendly and Dr Reddy is amazing.  We are lucky to know all of them.
All of the nurses were very friendly. Clean facilities and attentive. I highly recommend.

I have been calling to ask questions and to possibly make an appointment since last Friday.  It is now Tuesday and I am still unable to get anyone to answer the phone or to return my messages.  I have left 3 messages so far.  I have tried calling the New Patient line and the Established Patient line trying to get a live person to answer the phone but no one will answer the phone or call you back.  Bad for business and bad for patients!

Someone has streamlined your procedures.
Way to go
Excellent patient care service.  Dr. Kwak was attentive and involved in patient care.  Strongly recommended him for GI services.

I believe this practice has gone way down hill since Covid started. I don’t know what it is but it seems like Dr Reddy is away from the office more than he is at the office, like he is part time. When I do get to see him he isn’t friendly and thorough like he use to be. He also seems to be in a hurry to get you out. This visit he even forgot to tell me the results of my blood work for my fatty liver so I had to go back inside and ask the nurse, she looked it up and told me the results. The Dr told me to come back in 6 months but he put in computer 2 months.
The other problem is it is so hard to get someone on the phone. When you leave a message they say they will call you back within 24 hours. Don’t count it, I have never had a call back without me calling several times.
I use to love this practice but it has changed too much and not for the better.
Everything was wonderful. I really appreciate Dr.Reddy I do believe he will help my condition
Nurse Ashley was amazing. Super friendly and helpful. PA Laura Peterkin always takes the time to explain things.
Dr Hamat took him time to explain everything very well. The office staff were efficient and friendly.
Warm greeting. Wait was short. Pa was friendly and encouraging. Set appointments for test. Waiting on call for appointment time

On May 18, 2022 came in for 6 months visit.

The front desk lady was really rudely “Amber Aarcisse”. Was having issue to scan my temperature. She keeps asking me to lean forward so she can scan my forehead temperature. And she make no effort accomplish the task. (she make no effort to lean over scan my forehead). She keeps repeating saying she will Cancel/reschedule my appointment if I can not scan your temperature forehead.

(My forehead temperature was 95%)

Amber is rudely, have no customer experience. Not friendly. Unprofessional.

I would give ZERO STAR if there is an option. SUPER INEXPERIENCED and RUDE STAFF. Especially front desk receptionists. Because they work there they want to tell you what to do instead listen to you what you have to say. The location at North Houston 275 Lantern Bend suite # 200 Houston Texas 77090. When you call in it will take a long time to answer and sometime they even hang up on you. (They want to tell you what to do instead listen to you what you have to say.) Not sure how they earn the job!

In addition: the Nurse are highly recommended. They return my call when I left a voicemails within the same day.

The doctor and the nurse are wonderful. The front office is not warm. I never provide feedback but this time I wanted. I was told that I had a credit. I asked how much credit I have and she said… enough to cover your due. Very cold, not friendly at all. I believe when you go to the doctor you want to be welcome by  genuine, nice people as this is the first step.

Had an office visit today at 9:00am & was very nervous due to me not having insurance at the moment. This office still welcomed me with open arms, gave me A-1 treatment and gave me some options to look at so I could services immediately. I am overly happy with coming to this location. Ms.Amber the office supervisor was superb, so was Mrs.Charlene at the front desk and Ms.Ashley who attended me in the back. Also thank you to Ms.Laura the Nurse Practitioner who assisted me with my health concerns. You ladies rock and I thank you all so very much. If your having any Digestive, Liver or colon concerns please come here. You won’t regret it👌🏾

These guys are a pleasure to work with! Very attentive, explain things in detail, friendly staff and take the time to answer questions rather than rushing you out of the door. I’d fully recommend these guys to anyone.
The nurses  was very kind and all my needs  .my experience was very good.

The staff has always gone above & beyond to accommodate patients & I am very grateful for this.
I appreciate Dr Reddy for explaining things to me in a timely manner.

Medical staff is great. My issue is with just the office visit pay itself. I call and asked how much would it be for the visit and was told $80 and the plus if you do any labs or test. Then I go to see where I pay for the lab fee and im told that it would be $60 more because your a new patient. $60 more didn't include the lab fee that was just extra for the doctor consultation. Why wasn't I informed of that when I asked before I made the appointment. So for a new patient visit the total was $140 without insurance. Just talking to the lady cost $140. Thats fine just wished I was informed about that before the visit.
Doctor was right nice. But Tiffany was horrible. I wish I could talk to someone else. She is very Inconsiderate and hateful

The front office assistant was friendly and helpful.
Dr Mohamed is knowledgeable and explained to me the results from my previous procedure.

Unfortunately the PA was very cold and
unfriendly.She called my name and never said anything until when I got to room and all I heard  Stand on the scale.

I believe we say hello general introduction period.Am in the healthcare field.
The worst thing she stood up after whatever she did on the computer and left the room.

It was my second visit and I felt i wasn’t welcomed.
I had loved the place and here i Am rewinding what took place.
Nobody to help with Spanish speaking patients. Had to cancel appointments for grandma because they don’t speak Spanish in the office.

Props to Connie De Los Reyes, nurse practitioner, who explained things to me, and for scheduling/recommending  needed follow up testing. The person who interviewed me and took vital signs was great, as was the lab person. Thank y'all.
Best service from the front desk, nurse, lab-tech, and doctor. Doctor listen to all my concerns and was very polite.

Nice building, very warm and friendly front staff and assistants. Dr. Hamat was very knowledgeable, thorough, and I liked his treatment plan for me. I was brought back right away and had to wait but didn’t mind since I was in a private room and I prefer doctors that don’t rush through their patients.
My visit was very pleasant, receptions was professional, waiting period was excellent.

I was treated with respect by friendly staff member who took my insurance information and my temperature. Then she gave me forms to fill. After I completed the forms, I waited for a few minutes. Then I was called back to the examination room. I spoke with the Nurse Practitioner. She talked with me about the issues I have. Then she wrote prescriptions for my medications. I went to the check out desk and set up my next appointment.

The front office staff and the nurse were great, my issue is with the doctor. Did not pay any attention or listen to what I had to say, left me in worse condition prior to him walking in the door, did not pay any attention to what medication I take and decided to prescribe give me wrong dosages without discussing it with me (the patient). After spending the high amount of money to see this “doctor”, I want my money back since he was not helpful and there was no treatment whatsoever provided. Start looking for a new doctor who will listen, help, and provide quality care.
Staff were so kind and caring.
Doctor and nurse listened in detail.  Treatment plan to date is a work in progress, but progress is being made.

I live 35 minutes from Digestive & Liver Disease Consultants. However, the drive was worth it due to my consultation & procedure with Dr. Hamat in a beautiful, state of the art facility. I was well cared for, safe, & knew I had superior care.

This facility has always been very professional and patient oriented. I’ve been going here for nine years and it’s always been a good experience. I’m not real trustful of the medical industry as a whole. But when I go here for a procedure I have all the confidence in the world they will have my best interest in mind.

I saw Dr. Hamat at DLDC Lantern  Bend this week. His staff was prompt in checking me in and I had a minimal wait time before seeing the doctor. He was thorough in examining me and very attentive to my concerns. I highly recommend Dr. Hamat for your digestive issues.

Excellence experience at Digestive and Liver Disease Consultants.  Dr always listens to my issues then takes time to give you his opinion of what needs to be done.  I would recommend everyone to visit.

Always professional ,staff help Mrs. Ronda is a great help in her quick response to E-mail and no question to small or big that is greatly appreciated, as for Doctor Hammet very helpful ,caring and enjoy specking to him  overall a great staff and would recommend him to everyone

All of the employees was on point they seem to be having good order and in a timely fashion and telling you the same information so when the next person call it's what they said was going to happen
I appreciate that thank you
Staff very nice and explain testing didnt have to wait long

Dr. Hamat and his staff are the best!!  Always on time and I know they’re smiling….even behind a mask!  I feel completely confident in how Dr. Hamat arrives at a diagnosis and presents options to take care of the issues.

I am 75 years old and I have had many procedures done with many other doctors. Previously most we adquate thought at your medical center I was treated very professional and just as important very friendly. I felt very comfortable and certainly would recommend and will your organization to my friends and family. Thank you.
Staff and Doctors are great. Everyone is professional and friendly!
Great visit/staff despite long wait times.

Everything went very smoothly. Everybody actually called me by the name I go by. Everybody was conscientious about making me comfortable. One of the best experiences I've had.. and I've had a A lot of test done in my 60 years.
We were greeted in a friendly and professional way at the reception, helped with any information we needed and had appointment on time.   Staff in the clinic were also friendly and professional.
Very friendly,  professional staff. Very happy with Dr. Hamat and the care he provides.
Staff is sooooo helpful. Make you feel comfortable. Good people

Always an excellent experience. Dr. Hamat and his team listen to me describe my problems with UC. Then Dr. Hamat explains the options to take.   I have been seeing him for 8 years for UC. When a medicine stops being effective on me he moves me on to another as soon as possible. I realize there is no cure for UC. Dr. Hamats and his team provides me with excellent treatment/management of my disease. Big thank you to everyone there

Larry G.
Laura Peterkin knowledgeable and caring, I'm glad I found her

I have seen Katie Bycura 3 times now, and have always found her to be professional, knowledgeable, and friendly.  She doesn’t make you feel rushed.  She explains everything and answers all questions.
I also like Dr. Hamat, the anesthesiologist, and nursing staff at the surgery center who attended to me during my biopsy. They are all very attentive and professional.
My only complaint is that I was not able to have my husband come back with me when I got my liver biopsy results.  We were both wearing masks, and I told them we’ve both had the COVID vaccine.  I think there should be EXCEPTIONS. Talking on the phone doesn’t cut it.
CORRECTION UPDATE:  My husband was not able to come back into Katie’s office with me for biopsy results.  This is where I think there should be an EXCEPTION as there was a lot of information to absorb and also questions.  Coming alone for a regular appointment is fine. The surgery center was great.  They did let him come back shortly before I was ready to leave.
The employees were very friendly and helpful.
I was last at this office 5 years ago.  When I came this week I appreciated how I was treated with kindness and respect. Katie listened to me and suggested what could be done to help me.

Very poor customer service. Couldn’t reach them for couple days. After like 10 calls rude lady picked up i told her i could barely hear her. She told me to call back, afterwards I couldn’t reach them again. They never pickup phone calls.
The staff here is really great. From the front desk to the back, everyone was kind and caring. I was very happy with my experience here.

My mom is a new patient. We visited the Doctors office 1 week ago today. She has to have an upper and lower GI before she have have stint surgery. One is blocked 90%.
The nurse advised they would back with her the next day after her Dr. approved the procedure. NO phone call. I called her Dr on Monday to see if they approved the procedure and they did. NO calls. I have left messages and emailed to nurse. NO response. Mom needs the procedure to fix her blockage.
Going to look for a different Doctor this morning who will respond to phone calls.

First review was on the office lobby.  Dr. Hamat and the anesthesiologist did a great job in doing the colonoscopy. Fusha, his nurse?,  was very attentive.
Thank you!

I was called to schedule a colonoscopy because my 5 years follow was due.  I scheduled the appointment then was told it would be a teleconference sure to COVID.  At the time I asked the price and the staff member could not tell me.  The day off my 'teleconference' came and I had not received any directions on how this would occur, just the time.  When the time came and no call, not information I called the office.  At that time I was told in a not so nice tone, that I would receive a phone call.  20 mins later, a woman, I'm assuming the PA, called and in another not so nice tone told me me I had missed my appointment!  I told her I have been waiting to hear from them since before 8 o'clock.  I asked her what number were they using to call me and she gave me my work number.  I asked her why they will be using my work number when they initially called my cell phone number which was a number she had just called.  Then when she gave me directions on how to connect to the call it was very difficult to do that.  Finally got on the call it took about 5 minutes.  The PA told me that someone be calling to set up my colonoscopy appointment.  that was more than a month ago and I have not heard from anyone and I got a $172 bill for a 5 minute phone call.  My FSA asked for documentation of the 'visit'.  When I cled and asked for a receipt the receptionist was VERY rude. I was highly disappointed in all all aspects of the service I received from this staff.   I will be disputing the charge and asking for a refund.   I will be taking my business elsewhere.
I felt very confident in his ability as a doctor.  He was professional and straight-forward.  Did not push surgery for a huge liver cyst.

Update 3/9/20
Michelle had emailed me Friday. I just called spoke to her. She explained the issue and assured me everything was taken care of. I appeciate so much the time it took to thoroughly explain the issue.
3/6/20
I was assured by Teresa, the billing manager, that my insurance issues were resolved. Unfortunately that is not the case. I just received a bill that they clearly filed on the wrong insurance. So frustrating. It messes up my deductible issue when visiting other providers. I am VERY frustrated and angry.
3/6 PM I was just contacted by billing. Hopefully this will be resolved next week.

Update 2/17/20
I wish I could award 5 stars. If this review were based only on medical providers, I would. Dr. Reddy and his PA Laura P. are caring, competent professionals. Unfortunately, my experience with the billing/insurance department has been less than satisfactory. For the visit 1/17, I received a claim in the mail for an insurance company I do not even have! Even though I provided correct updated information prior to my visit and my updated cards at the visit. No one has explained the issue. I would like an explanation to set my mind at ease. Additionally, the billing department is VERY hard to reach. When I finally did so, the person was very  nice, but had no idea as to why the problem came about. I have reached out to various people without a return call or email.
Teresa, the billing manager called today and reassured me all is well. I appreciated that so very much.
My consultation was short sweet and to the point. All my questions were answered and my colonoscopy was scheduled the very next week

The PA we've been seeing is WONDERFUL.  However, the support staff is not the best at responding to emails or returning phone calls (still).  I complained previously about this and they got better but I'm having issues with them refunding me monies now for overpaying and all I'm getting is non-response.  Reached out to Blue Cross and Blue Shield and Accolade and they both are getting non-response.  Way to treat your paying customers by not refunding monies even when you admitted that I had a credit.
Excellant service my first time   great service

Great practice. Dr. Hamat is straightforward, sincere and easy to talk to. And I found his staff to be helpful, pleasant and friendly.  Everything you look for when you’re trying to deal with a series medical issue.  I’d recommend this group to my family and friends anytime!
Great office and staff, wait times tend to be long

Tube mi colonoscopia el 31 de Enero, el Dr Sha la hizo, desde que llegue a las 7:15 AM me atendieron muy bien. Mi cita era a las 7:30 . Fuero exacta, las enfermeras muy amables y atentas. Me dijeron el proceso, antes de la cirugía habló conmigo el Dr, el anestesista, el ayudante y la enfermera de cabecera. Me siento bien gracias a Dios no tuve ninguna molestia. Me dieron el resultado por el día lunes, y era en dos semanas que iba a tener los resultados.
Todo a sido muy bien, gracias a Dios, el lugar estaba muy adecuado para todo y muy limpio. Gracias por atenderme y hacerme sentir muy bien. Att Sogenor Ramos

I was very happy with Dr. Reyes who seemed to care about me. I’ve been looking for a doctor that has bedside manner and was very professional. She has both of these characteristics and I am looking forward to continuing my search for relief of my Illness.
Friendly staff, answered my questions, provided info. I could not be any happier on my first-time visit. Keep up the good work!

Very friendly staff and awesome doctors! The main location is very state of the art, with a surgery center connected to it so it's very convenient when scheduling procedures. I would highly recommend this practice to my friends and family.
These doctors are only in in it for the money.  I even had to report them to my insurance company for patient negligence.  They treated horribly in hospital and never calls back.

I have been a patient of Dr. Reddy for probably 25 yrs.  While I love Dr. Reddy, he has begun to limit his time in his practice, meaning he is out of the country or not in his practice more than he is in.  In the last month, I had to go to the hospital for severe stomach pain in upper abdomen region.  Cats can done shower some swelling in intestines and I was told to follow up with Gastro doc.  I did so and here's what happened.  Never saw a doctor for problem, Laura PA said to have endoscopy.   Since Dr. Reddy was not available, I had procedure with Dr. Shaw.  He told me and my husband that I had a polyp in intestine and some irritation  in my stomach. .  He said he did do biopsy but was not comfortable removing polyp because it was in a bloody place.  He referred me back to Dr.  Reddy  and that was  it.   He never told me about any meds I would be taking or anything else.  After not being called for a couple of days, I called to leave message for Dr. Reddys assistant.  I was was not happy that no one had followed up with me.  Laura, the PA returned my call and began to defend their actions saying we normally follow up with people after two days and she began to tell me that I would be taking several new meds. she said doc told me I had erosions in stomach and I would be taking several meds for that, nausea, and a new med for constipation that works better for my situation.  At that point I had not gone to bathroom for 5 days.  I was concerned  but continued with her protocol.  This is the eighth  day and still no movement.  Laura began to blame me saying that I was not interested in taking that family of meds, which I was taking for 3 days straight with an added laxative, and no results.  When I told Laura that she was lying about me not wanting to take the new meds because I clearly was, she hung up on me.  Why are these people not seeing a red flag.  There is a problem here and they are not addressing it.

Felt very safe, secure and calm all the way. I was wheeled into examination room, saw my doctor and the next thing I knew was I was awake in the attendant's room, my exam over with, and awaiting the arrival of the person who would be taking me home.

The place was fine! The staff was really nice! I just had an issue with being there at 9a and never left there until 1230p for a procedure that takes 15 minutes tops! A lot of waiting for no reason at all! They schedule too many at one time!

Dr. Redding and Staff are customer Oriented and always professionals.  I really appreciate the patience and concern they have given on my every visit.
Excellent service,
Thanks
All of the staff were very friendly. They answered all questions and explained everything they were doing and what to expect. This is good place to have any procedure you may need.
I did not like the results I was given about a presidure. I was given a prescription that cost 1100 dollars a month which I can, t afford, so said to myself forget it.
Thanks,to the doctor and staff at the Digestive&Liver Disease Medical Center.Dr.Howard and staff really made be comfortable and relaxed . Thank you for a wonderful job and taking care of my health.

My name is Luis Lopez i just want to let you  know that my doctor is a great doctor. She took her time to explain and show me what I have. She is a very excellent doctor and with the medication she order I feel 100% better. Thank you very much for seeing me and and explaining everything.

I had an excellent experience at this facility.  Staff was excellent. Waited longer than I would have liked but that was not at the fault of anyone,  procedures sometimes can run longer than expected. I highly recommend this facility.
The entire staff is so good.  Dr. Hamet  is a terrific surgeon.  The facility is clean and everyone is helpful and friendly.
Dr Hamat and his staff are the best. Always feel like they really care about me and my situation.

I just have to share my great experience at this facility! I was able to have a colonoscopy and stomach scope during the same visit! My nurse, Summer, came in, introduced herself, and explained everything first. Summer was also in the procedure room and kept me comfortable with conversation. I woke up to Jolie, another nurse, that explained everything, and got me ready to leave.  The doctor consulted with me, then out there door.  Ran like a well oiled machine! I referred my mother, and took her there. Summer remembered me, I was impressed. Thank you all!

This reflects Dr. Shah- not his partner. He is UNSAFE! If I could give ZERO stars I would. As a medical professional I was horrified at his bedside manner. My family member was in the hospital incredibly sick. That person is a nurse #1) They skipped days and FORGOT to round- the other members of the team(hospitalist, nurses, consulting doctors) were just as surprised as we were- as it was a GI consult they called and needed to figure out what was going on #2) After 3 days and multiple calls his partner came to round and said “pt. clear to discharge after advancing diet if tolerated.” My family member could not EAT let alone stand due to significant symptoms and GI related issues. The attending rounded in the afternoon and refused to discharge due to unsafe vitals and stability. Another two days pass and they had multiple calls due to forgetting to round. His partner then came again, and at least prescribed medications and monitoring. Another two days and Dr. shah, who maybe forgot what it means to be a doctor or be sick- due to failing to recall his Hippocratic oath, to failing to “DO NO HARM” comes in and in front of us -with my family member crying and down 18lbs due to GI symtoms -while IN THE HOSPITAL two weeks ( this isn’t a pre existing condition- the team was waiting on GI to make the calls as it was GI in nature, there’s a chain of command and respect, and the attending ordered all the tests within their scope of practice) this man Shah says “ Could I do something? Probably, but I’m not going too. I doubt we would find anything anyways. Maybe it’s in your head?” We remain polite and think maybe there’s a misunderstanding. My family member through tears asks about symptom control and how could it couldn’t possibly be in “their head” as the nurses and doctors attending have also agreed something serious was going on. It would cause episodes in the middle of the night, nurses called made notes. He responds “ honestly, I don’t like driving 15 minutes out of my way to come here. We both have too, and I would have refused your case had you not have previously been a patient of my partners.” Compassion- none. Bedside manner- terrible. Medical intervention- nothing. An inconvenience. It took all I had not to utter every angry word under the sun at this heartless individual with what seems to be a complex. Another family members says is there anything you can do please? Shah says “ I mean maybe we can just give you a pill and you may have to deal with this for life or maybe not. Either way I’m not doing anything else.” So with that, the nurse in the room immediately called the attending. A second consult was brought in and within a day tests were underway and surgery was performed.
I couldn’t be more disgusted in Shahs bedside manner. Dr. Hamat came in twice and at least was at the bedside after realizing his previous order of discharging wasn’t best plan of care- he came back. Regardless - Shah- was unprofessional, unsafe, and I cannot imagine who this man thinks he is. If you didn’t want the case due to a “15 minute drive” you decline the case- you don’t leave someone dwindling physically and in pain because it doesn’t suit you?! Awful bedside manner. Awful practice. More concerned with asking my family member where they lived then treatment. Grossly negligent.
You got into the field to help people I hope, maybe you forgot how. Here is your reminder. Treat people like people, if it was your family memeber laying in that bed, I hope to God they get compassionate thorough care- I wouldn’t wish your bedside manner on anyone.
Great staff, caring support staff and so grateful for Doc.'s.  Blessings to all🙋.

I give them 10 STARS!
VERY PLEASANT EXPERIENCE.
THE TECHNICIAN WAS FRIENDLY, PROFESSIONAL, AND COURTEOUS.

SINCERELY,
JERIDFRENCH
These guys really treated me well . Awesome staff and great care taken of me
I keep being harassed by this office over $25, I’ve never even been there. It’s ridiculous that they are constantly blowing up my phone.
Very professional and organized. About as good of an experience with a colonoscopy as possible.

Doctor Reddy is awesome. I finally found a doctor who listens to my symptoms. I highly recommend Digestive & Liver Disease. I have been to every doctor & specialist around. Spent tons of money on test with never an answer. Doctor Reddy diagnosed me right away.
The team gets a 5 star because they did  awesome job in a timely manner. I highly recommend that you  allow them to take care you in whatever you need they are qualified to do the job

I am a nurse and if you want a practice that is rude and had nurses that actually yell at you when in a mistake this practice is for you! Multiple instances of poor communication that wasted my time and money and caused me great discomfort! Nurse Megan is rude and cannot accept responsibility for her mistakes! When questioned with logical facts and  basic nursing procedures she chose to yell at me  in the office. Office manager agreed with all my complaints but no follow up! I gave her2 weeks! They have had 6 Dr leave the practice in short succession! I have been disappointed at the lack of continuity of care! Nurses blame mistakes on their inability to keep up with Dr. Orders! This is basic  Nursing 101. If you can’t keep up you stop before making mistakes and call someone that knows the answers! Instructing patients to do costly test and doing preps without orders is incompetent! I would have dropped this if they had been honest , not yelled at me and apologized! This is why insurance is so expensive! I hope this isn’t part of a plan to get patients to pay for tests? This use to be a great practice but it had not been managed well and they aren’t hiring safe competent staff! I’m extremely disappointed!
Everyone was warm, patience and helpful.

I wanted to share my experience I had at this facility.  I was scheduled for Endoscopy and Colonoscopy.  I was greeted by Sherrie, She was very genuinely kind and concerned with my well being.
My Nurse was Summer,  Summer was extremely thorough when it came to explaining my procedures and was very patient when it came to  answering any questions that I had. She was very professional and started my IV with one stick.  This sometimes is a chore.  I also appreciated the warm blankets. I can say these ladies worked together for the good of the patients.
Dr Reddy and His Staff are very professional and tentative with their patients.
Thank you for always taking care of me.

Very organized, efficient, knowledgeable and friendly.
I was treated like a queen by the receptionist, nurse, anesthesiologists, and Dr. Shah.
Thorough instructions were provided by the receptionist. The nurse brought warm blankets, inserted the IV and took my blood pressure while letting me know what to expect.
The anesthesiologist introduced himself and explained what he would do.
Dr Shah is the best.
I was very impressed with the checklist to make sure everyone was on the same page and truly appreciated the eye contact from everyone.
Thank you.
Very pleasent staff. The Dr. explained everything. Dr. Shah was willing to listen to my questions asked . He answer any question. Great personal service .

Having to have a colonoscopy was made much easier by Dr. Reddy and his office staff and the staff at the facility on Lantern Bend.  They took excellent care of me and I would highly recommend using them.
I'm completely satisfied with Dr Shaw and his staff.
